## Arc: Cinematic AI Launch (90s / 2700 frames at 30fps)
 
| Scene | Role | Duration | Frames | Energy Level |
|-------|------|----------|--------|-------------|
| 1. Hook | Bass drop + abstract visuals | 0–15s | 0–450 | 🔥 Max |
| 2. Problem / Context | Data noise, complexity, overwhelm | 15–40s | 450–1200 | ⚡ High, building |
| 3. Reveal | Product dashboard assembles | 40–70s | 1200–2100 | 🌊 Controlled climax |
| 4. Climax + CTA | Feature rapid-fire + logo + action | 70–90s | 2100–2700 | 🔥 Max again |
 
### Scene 1: Hook (0–15s | frames 0–450)
- Opens on **pure black** — 0.5s silence before bass hit
- First cut on beat drop — abstract neural network or particle field explodes into frame
- 3–5 rapid cuts (1.5–2s each) of abstract 3D visuals
- First text appears at beat hit #2 — bold claim, glitch entry
- No product yet — pure energy, curiosity, pattern interrupt
- Pacing: cut every 60–90 frames (2–3s)
 
### Scene 2: Problem / Context (15–40s | frames 450–1200)
- Visual metaphor: chaos, noise, overload — data flooding, fragmented screens, spinning without purpose
- Transition into this scene with a WHIP PAN or FLASH CUT from the hook
- 3–4 elements showing the problem — each 4–6s (120–180 frames)
- Typography slides in describing pain points — high velocity, no fade
- Ends with a FREEZE FRAME or slow-motion pull-back — the "inhale before the reveal"
- Pacing: slightly slower than hook (3–5s cuts) to let the problem land
 
### Scene 3: Reveal (40–70s | frames 1200–2100)
- Beat hit signals the transition — hard cut to dark background
- Product UI "assembles" from particles or geometric fragments — 3–4s assembly animation
- Dashboard fades/scales in — feels like unlocking something powerful
- Feature-by-feature reveal with UI close-ups — each feature gets 4–6s
- Camera moves: slow push-in on UI, orbit around 3D element, dramatic tilt reveal
- Use rim lighting glow on UI elements to make them feel premium
- Pacing: medium (4–6s cuts) — let the product breathe and impress
 
### Scene 4: Climax + CTA (70–90s | frames 2100–2700)
- Pace accelerates back to hook speed — rapid-fire feature montage (1–2s each)
- Beat sync: every cut lands ON the beat
- Logo reveal: spring animation, glow burst, 2–3s hold
- CTA text: largest text in video, glitch-in entry, holds for 5s
- Final frame: logo + tagline + URL on dark background — clean and confident
 
